    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Words or phrases, often descriptive or evocative, used to identify or provide reference to a work, including physical works, performances, literary works, and conceptual works. May apply to individual items or works, or to groups or series of items, in any medium. Titles may also be initials, numbers, or symbols. Examples are titles or names of works of art and architecture. For numeric or alphanumeric IDs or codes for uniquely identifying a work, prefer "identification numbers." To refer specifically to titles printed or inscribed on a book or other object, such as on the title page, prefer "titles (partial documents)."</Note_Text>
